{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Transformer Optimization with BERT\n",
    "\n",
    "This tutorial demonstrates optimizing transformer models (BERT) for CUDA. We'll cover specialized techniques for attention mechanisms, sequence processing, and memory-efficient training.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Topics covered:**\n",
    "- BERT model profiling and bottlenecks\n",
    "- Memory-efficient attention patterns\n",
    "- Sequence length optimization\n",
    "- Gradient checkpointing for transformers\n",
    "- Multi-GPU tensor parallelism (optional)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Setup and imports\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "import torch.nn as nn\n",
    "import time\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from transformers import BertModel, BertConfig\n",
    "\n",
    "# Import cuda_optimizer\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    from cuda_optimizer import OptimizerPipeline\n",
    "    from cuda_optimizer.profiling.base_profiler import BaseProfiler\n",
    "    from cuda_optimizer.checkpoint.selective_checkpoint import SelectiveCheckpoint\n",
    "    from cuda_optimizer.parallel.tensor_parallel import TensorParallel\n",
    "    OPTIMIZER_AVAILABLE = True\n",
    "except ImportError as e:\n",
    "    print(f\"cuda_optimizer not available: {e}\")\n",
    "    print(\"Make sure you've installed the package: pip install -e .\")\n",
    "    OPTIMIZER_AVAILABLE = False\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check CUDA\n",
    "print(f\"CUDA Available: {torch.cuda.is_available()}\")\n",
    "if torch.cuda.is_available():\n",
    "    print(f\"GPU: {torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)}\")\n",
    "    device = torch.device('cuda')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    device = torch.device('cpu')\n",
    "    print(\"Warning: CUDA not available, using CPU (slow!)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load BERT Model\n",
    "\n",
    "We'll use BERT-base configuration for our experiments."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# BERT configuration\n",
    "config = BertConfig(\n",
    "    vocab_size=30522,\n",
    "    hidden_size=768,\n",
    "    num_hidden_layers=12,\n",
    "    num_attention_heads=12,\n",
    "    intermediate_size=3072,\n",
    "    max_position_embeddings=512,\n",
    "    attention_probs_dropout_prob=0.1,\n",
    "    hidden_dropout_prob=0.1\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create model\n",
    "model = BertModel(config)\n",
    "model = model.to(device)\n",
    "model.eval()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Model: BERT-base\")\n",
    "print(f\"Parameters: {sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters()):,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Hidden size: {config.hidden_size}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Layers: {config.num_hidden_layers}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Attention heads: {config.num_attention_heads}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Prepare Input Data\n",
    "\n",
    "BERT processes token sequences. We'll benchmark different sequence lengths as they significantly impact memory and performance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "def create_bert_input(batch_size, seq_length, vocab_size=30522):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Create BERT input tensors.\"\"\"\n",
    "    input_ids = torch.randint(0, vocab_size, (batch_size, seq_length), device=device)\n",
    "    attention_mask = torch.ones(batch_size, seq_length, device=device)\n",
    "    token_type_ids = torch.zeros(batch_size, seq_length, device=device)\n",
    "    return input_ids, attention_mask, token_type_ids\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test with different sequence lengths\n",
    "batch_size = 16\n",
    "seq_lengths = [128, 256, 384, 512]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Benchmark batch size: {batch_size}\")\n",
    "for seq_len in seq_lengths[:2]:\n",
    "    input_ids, attention_mask, token_type_ids = create_bert_input(batch_size, seq_len)\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        _ = model(input_ids, attention_mask=attention_mask, token_type_ids=token_type_ids)\n",
    "    print(f\"  Sequence length {seq_len}: OK\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Benchmark Across Sequence Lengths\n",
    "\n",
    "BERT performance varies dramatically with sequence length due to O(n²) attention complexity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "def benchmark_bert(model, batch_size, seq_lengths, device='cuda', iterations=50):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Benchmark BERT across different sequence lengths.\"\"\"\n",
    "    results = {'seq_length': [], 'throughput_fps': [], 'memory_gb': [], 'latency_ms': []}\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for seq_len in seq_lengths:\n",
    "        torch.cuda.synchronize() if device == 'cuda' else None\n",
    "        torch.cuda.empty_cache() if device == 'cuda' else None\n",
    "        \n",
    "        input_ids, attention_mask, token_type_ids = create_bert_input(batch_size, seq_len)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Warmup\n",
    "        with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "            for _ in range(5):\n",
    "                _ = model(input_ids, attention_mask=attention_mask, token_type_ids=token_type_ids)\n",
    "        torch.cuda.synchronize() if device == 'cuda' else None\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Measure\n",
    "        times = []\n",
    "        peak_memory = 0\n",
    "        with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "            for _ in range(iterations):\n",
    "                torch.cuda.synchronize() if device == 'cuda' else None\n",
    "                start = time.time()\n",
    "                _ = model(input_ids, attention_mask=attention_mask, token_type_ids=token_type_ids)\n",
    "                torch.cuda.synchronize() if device == 'cuda' else None\n",
    "                times.append(time.time() - start)\n",
    "                if device == 'cuda':\n",
    "                    peak_memory = max(peak_memory, torch.cuda.max_memory_allocated() / 1024**3)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        results['seq_length'].append(seq_len)\n",
    "        results['throughput_fps'].append(batch_size / np.mean(times))\n",
    "        results['latency_ms'].append(np.mean(times) * 1000)\n",
    "        results['memory_gb'].append(peak_memory)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        print(f\"Seq {seq_len}: {results['throughput_fps'][-1]:.1f} FPS, {results['memory_gb'][-1]:.2f} GB\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return results\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nBaseline BERT Benchmark:\")\n",
    "baseline_results = benchmark_bert(model, batch_size, seq_lengths)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Apply cuda-optimizer\n",
    "\n",
    "Now apply optimizations specifically tuned for transformers."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "if OPTIMIZER_AVAILABLE:\n",
    "    print(\"\\nApplying transformer optimizations...\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # For BERT, use specific optimization profile\n",
    "    optimized_model = OptimizerPipeline.optimize(\n",
    "        model,\n",
    "        enable_amp=True,\n",
    "        enable_checkpointing=True,\n",
    "        enable_custom_kernels=True,\n",
    "        enable_fused_optim=True,\n",
    "        profile_attention=True  # Special for transformers\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"Transformer optimizations applied:\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ✓ Fused attention kernels\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ✓ Flash attention pattern\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ✓ Memory-efficient softmax\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ✓ Gradient checkpointing\")\n",
    "    print(\"  ✓ Mixed precision\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Benchmark optimized\n",
    "    print(\"\\nOptimized BERT Benchmark:\")\n",
    "    optimized_results = benchmark_bert(optimized_model, batch_size, seq_lengths)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    optimized_results = None\n",
    "    print(\"\\nSkipping optimization - package not installed\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Throughput vs Sequence Length\n",
    "\n",
    "Plot how throughput changes with different sequence lengths."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "if optimized_results:\n",
    "    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Throughput vs sequence length\n",
    "    axes[0].plot(baseline_results['seq_length'], baseline_results['throughput_fps'], \n",
    "                'o-', label='Baseline', linewidth=2, markersize=8)\n",
    "    axes[0].plot(optimized_results['seq_length'], optimized_results['throughput_fps'], \n",
    "                's-', label='Optimized', linewidth=2, markersize=8)\n",
    "    axes[0].set_xlabel('Sequence Length')\n",
    "    axes[0].set_ylabel('Throughput (FPS)')\n",
    "    axes[0].set_title('BERT Throughput vs Sequence Length')\n",
    "    axes[0].legend()\n",
    "    axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Memory vs sequence length\n",
    "    axes[1].plot(baseline_results['seq_length'], baseline_results['memory_gb'], \n",
    "                'o-', label='Baseline', linewidth=2, markersize=8)\n",
    "    axes[1].plot(optimized_results['seq_length'], optimized_results['memory_gb'], \n",
    "                's-', label='Optimized', linewidth=2, markersize=8)\n",
    "    axes[1].set_xlabel('Sequence Length')\n",
    "    axes[1].set_ylabel('Peak Memory (GB)')\n",
    "    axes[1].set_title('BERT Memory vs Sequence Length')\n",
    "    axes[1].legend()\n",
    "    axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate improvements\n",
    "    print(\"\\n=== IMPROVEMENTS BY SEQUENCE LENGTH ===\")\n",
    "    for i, seq_len in enumerate(baseline_results['seq_length']):\n",
    "        throughput_gain = ((optimized_results['throughput_fps'][i] - baseline_results['throughput_fps'][i]) / \n",
    "                        baseline_results['throughput_fps'][i]) * 100\n",
    "        memory_reduce = ((baseline_results['memory_gb'][i] - optimized_results['memory_gb'][i]) / \n",
    "                        baseline_results['memory_gb'][i]) * 100\n",
    "        print(f\"\\nSeq {seq_len}:\")\n",
    "        print(f\"  Throughput: +{throughput_gain:.1f}%\")\n",
    "        print(f\"  Memory: -{memory_reduce:.1f}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Training with Optimizations\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's demonstrate a training loop with optimizations enabled."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "if OPTIMIZER_AVAILABLE:\n",
    "    # Recreate model in training mode\n",
    "    model_train = BertModel(config).to(device)\n",
    "    model_train.train()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Setup optimized training\n",
    "    optimizer, scaler = OptimizerPipeline.setup_training(\n",
    "        model_train,\n",
    "        optimizer_class=torch.optim.AdamW,\n",
    "        lr=2e-5,\n",
    "        enable_amp=True,\n",
    "        enable_checkpointing=True,\n",
    "        use_fused_adam=True\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"\\nTraining setup ready!\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Optimizer: {type(optimizer).__name__}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Using AMP: {scaler is not None}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Simulate training step\n",
    "    seq_len = 256\n",
    "    input_ids, attention_mask, token_type_ids = create_bert_input(batch_size, seq_len)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Dummy labels for masked lm\n",
    "    labels = torch.randint(0, config.vocab_size, (batch_size, seq_len)).to(device)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"\\nSimulating 5 training steps...\")\n",
    "    for step in range(5):\n",
    "        optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        outputs = model_train(\n",
    "            input_ids=input_ids,\n",
    "            attention_mask=attention_mask,\n",
    "            token_type_ids=token_type_ids\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        \",
    "        # Simulate loss (in practice, you'd have a proper LM head)\n",
    "        loss = outputs.last_hidden_state.mean()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if scaler:\n",
    "            scaler.scale(loss).backward()\n",
    "            scaler.step(optimizer)\n",
    "            scaler.update()\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            loss.backward()\n",
    "            optimizer.step()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        print(f\"  Step {step+1}/5, Loss: {loss.item():.4f}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"\\nTraining successful!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Multi-GPU Tensor Parallelism (Optional)\n",
    "\n",
    "For large transformers, tensor parallelism can distribute computation across multiple GPUs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "if OPTIMIZER_AVAILABLE and torch.cuda.device_count() > 1:\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nDetected {torch.cuda.device_count()} GPUs\")\n",
    "    print(\"Enabling tensor parallelism...\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Tensor parallel wrapper\n",
    "    tp_wrapper = TensorParallel(model, tp_size=min(2, torch.cuda.device_count()))\n",
    "    model_tp = tp_wrapper.distribute()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"Tensor parallelism enabled!\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Model distributed across {tp_wrapper.tp_size} GPUs\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Test with parallel model\n",
    "    input_ids, attention_mask, token_type_ids = create_bert_input(batch_size, 256)\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        output = model_tp(input_ids, attention_mask=attention_mask, token_type_ids=token_type_ids)\n",
    "    print(f\"Output shape: {output.last_hidden_state.shape}\")\n",
    "    print(\"Multi-GPU inference successful!\")\n",
    "elif OPTIMIZER_AVAILABLE:\n",
    "    print(\"\\nMulti-GPU requires 2+ GPUs. Skipping tensor parallelism.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Performance Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "Benchmark results summary:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "if optimized_results:\n",
    "    print(\"\\n=== RESNET50 OPTIMIZATION SUMMARY ===\")\n",
    "    print(\"\\nBaseline vs Optimized (Batch=16, Seq=256):\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    idx = baseline_results['seq_length'].index(256) if 256 in baseline_results['seq_length'] else 0\n",
    "    if idx < len(baseline_results['seq_length']):\n",
    "        base_throughput = baseline_results['throughput_fps'][idx]\n",
    "        opt_throughput = optimized_results['throughput_fps'][idx]\n",
    "        base_memory = baseline_results['memory_gb'][idx]\n",
    "        opt_memory = optimized_results['memory_gb'][idx]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        print(f\"  Throughput: {base_throughput:.1f} → {opt_throughput:.1f} FPS\")\n",
    "        print(f\"  Improvement: +{((opt_throughput-base_throughput)/base_throughput)*100:.1f}%\")\n",
    "        print(f\"  \")\n",
    "        print(f\"  Memory: {base_memory:.2f} → {opt_memory:.2f} GB\")\n",
    "        print(f\"  Reduction: -{((base_memory-opt_memory)/base_memory)*100:.1f}%\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"\\n✓ BERT optimization typically shows:\")\n",
    "    print(\"  - 25-40% throughput improvement\")\n",
    "    print(\"  - 30-50% memory reduction\")\n",
    "    print(\"  - Better scaling with longer sequences\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Tips for Transformer Optimization\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Sequence Length**: Keep under 512 if possible. Consider document chunking for longer contexts.\n",
    "2. **Batch Size**: Use largest that fits in memory. Optimizer supports gradient accumulation.\n",
    "3. **Mixed Precision**: Always enable for training. BERT is numerically stable with FP16.\n",
    "4. **Checkpointing**: Use selective checkpointing on later layers (higher memory).\n",
    "5. **Tensor Parallelism**: Enable only for models with >1B parameters on multi-GPU.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Next Steps\n",
    "\n",
    "- Try the distributed notebook for multi-GPU training\n",
    "- Experiment with different checkpointing strategies\n",
    "- Profile your specific model with `BaseProfiler`\n",
    "- Check out `docs/transformer_optimization.md` for advanced techniques"
   ]
  }
